<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-316-658  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 316 658.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  March 19 1990 v4 n11 p59(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Lights-out computing: agencies are discovering the benefits ofunattended computer centers.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pellerin, Cheryl.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Federal agencies are beginning to pursue automated operations inunattended computer centers as a response to diminishing budgets,growing workloads and the availability of increasinglysophisticated hardware and software.andP;  The federal trend isreflected in the Feb 28, 1991, release of the Council of FederalData Center Directors Committee on Lights-Out Computer Operations''Automated Operations Planning Guide.' The manual discusses theprocess and requirements of automated operations and the impactson personnel.andP;  Federal agencies turning to automated operationsinclude the House of Representatives' House Information Systems,Internal Revenue Service, the Environmental Protection Agency andthe Department of Defense.andP;  Automation activities at each of theagencies are discussed.andP;  Several automation products are alsobriefly described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AutomationGovernment AgencyTrendsImplementationComputer FacilitiesManagement of EDPUnited States. Internal Revenue ServiceUnited States. Environmental Protection AgencyUnited States. Department of Defense.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>